criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Ages 18 to 75;

          -  Unlimited gender;

          -  Patients with chronic hepatitis C treated with interferon combined with ribavirin (PR)
             antiviral therapy (PR therapy for 6 months or more) and / or direct antiviral drugs
             (DAAs). All patients with chronic hepatitis C met the diagnostic criteria of the
             Chinese Guidelines for the Prevention and Treatment of Chronic Hepatitis C (2015)

          -  No hormones and / or immunosuppressants and other hepatoprotective drugs;

          -  Sign a written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Combined with other hepatitis virus (HBV, HDV) infections;

          -  Immune liver disease;

          -  HIV infection;

          -  long-term alcohol and / or other liver damage drugs;

          -  mental illness;

          -  Evidence of liver tumor (liver cancer or AFP> 100 ng / ml);

          -  Decompensated cirrhosis;

          -  Those who have serious heart, brain, lung, kidney and other system diseases that
             cannot participate in long-term follow-up;

          -  There are hormones and / or immunosuppressants and other hepatoprotective drugs.
